(551, '86.168.108.90', 1362057259, 704, 0, 'Question #704: I\\\'m reporting question #704 because ... blah blah testing', 4),
(2, '109.149.198.135', 1333017336, 408, 0, 'Question #408: I\\\'m reporting question #408 because ... testing', 2),
(3, '109.149.198.135', 1333017391, 540, 0, 'Question #540: I\\\'m reporting question #540 because ...', 3),
(4, '109.149.198.135', 1333018266, 488, 0, 'Question #488: I\\\'m reporting question #488 because ... Testing the report', 1),
(5, '64.68.48.125', 1333059714, 703, 0, 'Question #703: I\\\'m reporting question #703 because ...\r\n\r\nhttp://www.rollerderbyruleoftheday.com/2011/05/6164-illegal-interference-in-game-play.html', 1),
(6, '216.235.121.247', 1333061049, 61, 0, 'Question #61: I\\\'m reporting question #61 because ... according to 2.5.1, there is 1 minute between overtime jams, so it should be specified in this question that it is assuming a non overtime jam.', 3),
(7, '77.102.210.58', 1333093219, 517, 0, 'Question #517: I\\\'m reporting question #517 because ... the question doesn\\\'t give sufficient game impact to be assessed properly.', 3),
(8, '77.102.210.58', 1333093671, 461, 0, 'Question #461: I\\\'m reporting question #461 because ... no game impact in question to assess this penalty.', 3),
(9, '63.246.190.102', 1333126410, 423, 0, 'Question #423: Sorry, I just noticed this option, so I don\\\'t know which question it is, but I have quoted the entire question below:\r\n\r\n\\"True or False: You can use your elbows to \\"hook\\" another player.\\"\r\n\r\nIt\\\'s technically true IF the other player is not an opposing player AND your hooking elbows does not impede any opposing players. So it really should specify \\"an opposing player\\" in order for false to be the correct answer. HTH!', 2),
(10, '63.246.190.102', 1333132452, 608, 0, 'Question #608: I\\\'m reporting question #608 because ... \r\n\r\nIf the skater is actually skating out of bounds, as the phrase \\"skates out of bounds\\" implies, it could be a skating out of bounds penalty.  If you rephrase it to state \\"misses and goes out of bounds\\" I think it would be more correct.', 3),
(11, '63.246.190.102', 1333140849, 165, 0, 'Question #165: I\\\'m reporting question #165 because ... \r\nthey need to re-pass all of the blockers LEGALLY- if they re-pass and commit another penalty, they still can\\\'t be lead.', 3),
(12, '94.192.187.247', 1333187199, 604, 0, 'Question #604: I\\\'m reporting question #604 because ... What about \\"6.11.15 - An in bounds, upright and skating skater who has re-entered the track from out of bounds in front of the foremost in-play opposing Blocker, which results in her having bettered her position.\\"', 1),
(13, '94.192.187.247', 1333195400, 827, 0, 'Question #827: I\\\'m reporting question #827 because ... What about an offical review?', 3),
(14, '66.65.191.187', 1333200465, 213, 0, 'Question #213: I\\\'m reporting question #213 because ... typo in one of the answers. Shot should be short.', 2),
(15, '76.3.225.138', 1333311830, 63, 0, 'Question #63: I\\\'m reporting question #63 because ... 2.4.4 says:\r\n\r\n2.4.4 - If all skaters are not on the track and ready to start the next jam after the allotted time, the jam will start without the missing skater(s) and the team will skate short for that jam. If skaters are not in position on their start whistle they will be subject to false start penalties (see Section 6.13.5 and Section 6.13.16).\r\n\r\nTherefore, the answer is D.', 3),
(16, '86.22.243.80', 1333313941, 842, 0, 'Question #842: I\\\'m reporting question #842 because ... \\"referees\\" is spelt \\"referrers\\"', 2),
(17, '86.22.243.80', 1333314296, 174, 0, 'Question #174: I\\\'m reporting question #174 because ... \\"both skaters\\" should read \\"both jammers\\"', 2),
(18, '77.102.210.58', 1333372962, 584, 0, 'Question #584: I\\\'m reporting question #584 because ... not enough info. when returning from the box a jammer may enter in front of the other jammer, penalized, as long as she comes in behind the pack.', 3),
(19, '86.29.15.179', 1333401571, 474, 0, 'Question #474: I\\\'m reporting question #474 because ... maybe double negative wording \\"You can not legally block a skater\\", maybe \\"You can legally block a skater\\" or \\"You can not illegally block a skater\\" because the answer is you can block a skater with both skates off the ground, but true is wrong?', 3),
(20, '86.29.15.179', 1333404204, 438, 0, 'Question #438: I\\\'m reporting question #438 because ... the answer sould include something like \\"within 10 feet of a pack\\"', 1),
(21, '86.29.15.179', 1333441045, 638, 0, 'Question #638: I\\\'m reporting question #638 because ... this question doesn\\\'t state if the skater is a part of the pack or not.', 3),
(22, '86.29.15.179', 1333453506, 240, 0, 'Question #240: I\\\'m reporting question #240 because ... 3.4.6 reads, \\"if the halmet cover is removed by an opponents action, the jammer may replace the helmet cover and regain lead jammer status\\", unless your splitting hairs not having in the question that the jammer has put it back on or not??.... there are alot of questions like this that are not productive for learning!', 3),
(23, '86.29.15.179', 1333454644, 147, 0, 'Question #147: I\\\'m reporting question #147 because ... they only need to line up behind the pivots if the pivots are touching the pivot line(which doesn\\\'t happen every often) so really \\\'D\\\' is currently more accurate (or \\"Anywhere in front of the Jammers, sometimes behind the pivots\\").', 3),
(24, '86.29.15.179', 1333467266, 886, 0, 'Question #886: I\\\'m reporting question #886 because ... 9.2.11.1 \\"A Captain or Designated Alternative requests an Official Review\\" this suggests that if the captain isn\\\'t about the DA could do it, and therefor explain the grievance?, eventhough 9.2.11.4 doesn\\\'t say DA...', 2),
(25, '86.29.15.179', 1333475079, 900, 0, 'Question #900: I\\\'m reporting question #900 because ... i had a question on here i think to do with 7.5.2.4 (i think the wording was around the other way  though) and answered \\\'a major\\\', so my logic answering that one was using the \\\'is a ref\\\'s unsure they make the lesser call\\\' rule, i got it wrong, the answer being \\"referees may not downgrade an expulsion\\", so i used that info to answer this question and got this one wrong !! i think they need uniting some how..', 3),
(26, '65.61.72.23', 1333476644, 520, 0, 'Question #520: I\\\'m reporting question #520 because ... it doesn\\\'t mention \\"intentional, negligent, or reckless\\", which are requirements for the stopped block to be an expulsion.  See 6.9.12 and 6.9.16', 3),
(27, '86.29.15.179', 1333476712, 825, 0, 'Question #825: I\\\'m reporting question #825 because ... the question doesn\\\'t say if they are on there inital or scoring pass, \\\'A\\\' would be right if they were \\"still in the pack\\" on there inital pass', 1),
(28, '86.29.15.179', 1333482213, 498, 0, 'Question #498: I\\\'m reporting question #498 because ... maybe reword to \\"When exiting the penalty box skaters may only skate out of bounds in a counter-clockwise\\" or something as i took the question as in the only time a skater can skate counter-clockwise is when they are leaving the penalty box, whitch is true.... isn\\\'t it....', 3),
(29, '86.29.15.179', 1333483070, 198, 0, 'Question #198: I\\\'m reporting question #198 because ... i took \\\'returning\\\' as they had not \\\'returned\\\' 3.5.3.2 reads \\"jammers may transfer the star upon returning to play from the panalty box\\" - \\"returning from the penalty box\\" is different to \\"returning to play\\"', 2),
(30, '24.111.116.214', 1333488320, 728, 0, 'Question #728: I\\\'m reporting question #728 because ... it is poorly written. I\\\'m confused. Is there three blockers being penalized? or just the two?', 3),
(31, '71.79.33.24', 1333492116, 331, 0, 'Question #331: I\\\'m reporting question #331 because ... \r\n\r\nI think the answer is incorrect.  What about a skater who initiates positional blocking.  A skater skating clockwise and causes a jammer to skate around her has not made contact but blocked the path the jammer.  Yes?  No?', 1),
