(69, '71.23.91.114', 1335445493, 381, 0, 'Question #381: I\\\'m reporting question #381 because ... \r\n\r\nAlthough I understand the intent of this question, I don’t particularly agree with its wording. Technically, a skater gets a major penalty for habitually falling small in front of opponents after the third time. Meaning, she falls small a third time, and after it has happened the penalty is issued. So going by actual course of action, a skater can fall small three times before getting a major penalty for it, not twice. They can do so twice without getting a penalty at all, and then after the third time they get the penalty\r\n\r\nRDRotD', 2),
