(73, '72.15.28.210', 1335470145, 428, 0, 'Question #428: I\\\'m reporting question #428 because ... \r\n\r\nthe referenced rule states - 6.7.3 - Touching and assisting teammates that does not create a wall to impede an opponent or prevent receiving a block from an opponent is not a multi-player block.\r\n\r\nThe answer reads - Touching and assisting teammates to create a wall to prevent receiving a block from an opponent You Win! See rule 6.7.3 (view on WFTDA.com)\r\n\r\nthe question reads - Which of these is a multi-player block: \r\n\r\nThe rules states that touching and not creating a wall is NOT a penalty, but it does NOT state that the act of making a wall by doing this IS automatically a penalty.  Touching the arm of my team mate while in a wall, even if it impedes another skater is NOT a multi-player block.  I would have to be gripping their arm and the point where I am gripping them would have to be impeding the opposing skater.  Answer A in no inherently wrong, more detail needs to be provided for it to be a wrong answer.  \r\n\r\nThis issue has been discussed at length on Zebra huddle and the WFTDA has provided clarification on this.', 3),
