(110, '99.107.231.114', 1336689305, 833, 0, 'Question #833: I\\\'m reporting question #833 because ... \r\nI think this is an unnecessarily tricky question. I think there are valid arguments for either (b) or (c) as the correct answer; certainly they can\\\'t score on blockers in the new initial pass, but there is no \\"list of blockers that the jammer can\\\'t score on, because she scored on them in the previous pass/jam\\", and I think the question implies that there is.\r\n\r\nIt\\\'s obtuse to say that she \\"can\\\'t score on any blockers because it\\\'s an initial pass\\", when \\"she can score on all of the blockers, as soon as she finishes her initial pass.\\"\r\n\r\nFranky, I\\\'d just kill this question, and devise a couple of new ones that are more specific.', 3),
(111, '129.97.124.80', 1336759307, 604, 0, 'Question #604: I\\\'m reporting question #604 because ... Foremost blocker escalates it form a minor to a major.', 1),
