(128, '203.214.81.190', 1337151517, 442, 0, 'Question #442: I\\\'m reporting question #442 because ... \r\nThis question is poorly worded.  Rule 6.8.1 refers to Out Of Bounds Blocking.\r\nAll the answers above may be right depending on the situation.', 3),
(129, '203.214.81.190', 1337151819, 520, 0, 'Question #520: I\\\'m reporting question #520 because ...\r\nThis question is not worded correctly.  The have incorrectly used the adverbs \\\'intentionally\\\' and \\\'illegally\\\'.\r\n\r\n\r\n 6.9.20 - Intentional, negligent, or reckless contact with an opponent while stopped on the track in an illegal manner.', 3),
(130, '203.214.81.190', 1337152905, 363, 0, 'Question #363: I\\\'m reporting question #363 because ...\r\nIt has to be successful or egregious.\r\n\r\nThe following egregious acts will be automatic game expulsions, and can be punished as a multi-game suspension (see Section 7.5.2.2). Expulsions will be issued for a conscious, forceful attempt to block an opponent in the back egregiously, whether or not the action was successful.\r\n\r\n\r\n6.1.4 - Intentional, negligent, or reckless illegal contact to the back of an opponent, back of an opponent’s legs, or back of an opponent’s booty.\r\n\r\ngre·gious&#8194; &#8194;[ih-gree-juhs, -jee-uhs]  Show IPA\r\nadjective\r\n1.\r\nextraordinary in some bad way; glaring; flagrant: an egregious mistake; an egregious liar.\r\n2.\r\nArchaic . distinguished or eminent.\r\n', 1),
(131, '203.214.81.190', 1337153611, 560, 0, 'Question #560: I\\\'m reporting question #560 because ... \r\nPoorly worded answers.\r\nMaybe it should say :When they return to an in-bounds position and the skater is upright and skating.', 3),
