(135, '75.110.192.108', 1337203560, 380, 0, 'Question #380: I\\\'m reporting question #380 because ... \r\n\r\nIt is wrong, rules say three times - also rules sat tripping an opponent. I\\\'m not sure if you\\\'d call tripping on a teammate.', 2),
(136, '71.204.215.103', 1337225790, 380, 0, 'Question #380: I\\\'m reporting question #380 because ... According to 6.3.8 it is only 3 or more times during the course of a bout that habitual contact during the normal course of skating may begun to be called as Major penalties.\r\n\r\n\\"6.3.8 - Habitual contact, three or more times during the course of a bout, between skates and wheels that is part of the normal skating motion that causes an opposing skater to stumble or fall or lose her relative position. The intent is to penalize skaters whose normal skating motion is dangerous to her opponents. A single skater who repeatedly trips other skaters, even with her normal skating motion is adversely affecting game play and safety.\\"', 2),
(137, '203.20.33.97', 1337234492, 144, 0, 'Question #144: I\\\'m reporting question #144 because ... Hi! Great work on quiz! Just thinking that it\\\'s not mandatory to field a pivot, but if u do, it must be a blocker as it could not be a jammer. Is it just enough to ask \\\'is is mandatory to field a pivot?\\\' thanks!', 3),
