(300, '90.204.110.146', 1346102068, 817, 0, 'Question #817: I\\\'m reporting question #817 because ... I think the term \\\'extra point\\\' is misleading :) \r\n\r\nI know the jammer gets a point for opposing skaters returning from the penalty point behind them, but \\\'extra point\\\' kinda sounds like they\\\'re getting two points for those skaters.', 3),
(301, '12.54.94.21', 1346271609, 543, 0, 'Question #543: I\\\'m reporting question #543 because ... \r\n\r\nThe word \\"optional\\" has connotation in this question.  Standard Practices dictate that the referee *should* give the warning when capable.  The rules simply say that it doesn\\\'t take priority over penalties, and doesn\\\'t *have* to be given prior to giving penalties.  That doesn\\\'t mean the referee can decide to *never* give the warning, because it\\\'s their option.\r\n\r\nI think a better way of wording this question might be:\r\n\\"Out of play skaters may be warned that they are out of play, however, the referee doesn\\\'t need to warn the skaters prior to issuing Out Of Play penalties.\\"\r\n\r\nKeep up the good work!\r\n-Bob', 3),
(302, '124.169.222.16', 1346895108, 84, 0, 'Question #84: I\\\'m reporting question #84 because ... the correct answer is wrong, there are 30seconds between jams not 1 minute.', 1),
(303, '90.204.110.146', 1347010558, 393, 0, 'Question #393: I\\\'m reporting question #393 because ... Shoulsnt this be an expulsion if it was intentional?', 3),
