(305, '99.88.132.198', 1347372325, 201, 0, 'Question #201: I\\\'m reporting question #201 because ... States \\"True or False:\\" but is not a true or false question.', 3),
(306, '27.33.159.87', 1347764816, 480, 0, 'Question #480: I\\\'m reporting question #480 because ... I understand the rule behind this question is talking about contact made as the skater is re-entering. The wording of the question makes it unclear whether the re-entering of the track and the contact are sequential or simultaneous.', 3),
(307, '90.204.110.146', 1347875771, 634, 0, 'Question #634: I\\\'m reporting question #634 because ... The question is fine, but could you please add the link to the clarification for this one? It\\\'d be an awesome help :) Thank you! :D', 3),
(308, '81.136.225.110', 1347978680, 68, 0, 'Question #68: I\\\'m reporting question #68 because ... \r\nI think there is a typo in answer D.  It reads \\"If there is no jam cover currently in the jam\\"  Shouldn\\\'t it say helmet cover?', 3),
(309, '149.135.145.22', 1348207736, 85, 0, 'Question #85: I\\\'m reporting question #85 because ... \r\nRule 2.3.4 stipulates that if there is 30sec or less on the period clock then there will not be an overtime jam. It does not say if there is less than 30 sec. Therefore the best answers in this case would be any amount of seconds over 30sec, in this multi choice 50sec was the closest and it comes up as incorrect. I had the same question twice once with 49sec as an option and this too was states to be incorrect with 30sec being the said correct answer.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you SOOO much for this quite. It has been very very useful as a learning tool! :)', 2),
(310, '91.176.126.93', 1348425071, 95, 0, 'Question #95: I\\\'m reporting question #95 because ... \r\n\r\nWhat about overtime jams?', 3),
(311, '109.145.172.196', 1348660813, 568, 0, 'Question #568: I\\\'m reporting question #568 because its true when the iniating when the initiating skater downs herself or falls at any time after the initiating block a skater may  return in bounds in front of the skater who blocked her out of bounds, and no penalty is to be issued.', 3),
(312, '58.168.94.112', 1348757765, 670, 0, 'Question #670: I\\\'m reporting question #670 because ... The wording is confusing. It implies the real question is \\"what is the penalty for intentionally committing an illegal procedure.\\"\r\n\r\nIt should read something like \\"in relation to calling insubordination, what should be given to a player who intentionally commits an illegal procedure?\\"', 3),
