(335, '81.156.246.42', 1356823536, 1493, 0, 'Question #1493: I\\\'m reporting question #1493 because I think some words are missing? True or False: A Fouled Out skater can be substituted in the jam <if> they Foul Out in <order> to prevent their team skating short. P.S. I love Roller Derby Test O\\\'Matic! x\r\n\r\n\r\n', 3),
(336, '222.155.83.163', 1356830110, 1077, 0, 'Question #1077: I\\\'m reporting question #1077 because ... 3.3.3 - An inactive Jammer has the advantage of all Jammer abilities except scoring points (Section 8 - Scoring) and earning Lead Jammer status (Section 3.4 - Lead Jammer).', 3),
(337, '99.37.64.202', 1356847619, 533, 0, 'Question #533: If a skater\\\'s or group of skaters\\\' actions create a no-pack situation via \\"gradually deviating from the speed of the pack as established through game play,\\" \\"illegally destroying the pack penalties shall not be given.\\"\r\n\r\nSo the answer to this question should be false. Because they aren\\\'t always penalized for their actions. (See: Power jam \\"passive offense\\")\r\n\r\n6.10.2.1.1 - The rules do not define pack speed. Illegally destroying the pack penalties shall not be given for gradually deviating from the speed of the pack as established through game play, unless said deviation is sudden, rapid, and marked, leaving the opposing team no opportunity to adjust and maintain a pack.', 3),
(338, '80.229.2.190', 1356859529, 1130, 0, 'Question #1130: I\\\'m reporting question #1130 because ... \r\n\r\nGrammar rather than incorrect. The pack \\\'may\\\' start rolling, the question states \\\'does\\\'.\r\nThey don\\\'t have to. They can remain stopped after the whistle, or they can be moving before it.', 3),
(339, '87.194.199.126', 1356877264, 1221, 0, 'Question #1221: I\\\'m reporting question #1221 because ... the listed answer is Delay of Game cannot be No Impact/No Penalty as per 6.15.1 while Expulsion is listed as an incorrect answer, but according to 6.15.5 Delay of Game is also not expulsion worthy. So both are correct answers.', 2),
(340, '87.194.199.126', 1356878541, 1111, 0, 'Question #1111: I\\\'m reporting question #1111 because ... the correct answer listed is \\\'Expulsion or Suspension\\\', while \\\'Gross Misconduct penalty\\\' is listed as incorrect. But the expulsion or suspension falls under the category of Gross Misconduct penalties so both answers are valid.', 2),
(341, '87.194.199.126', 1356879951, 1495, 0, 'Question #1495: I\\\'m reporting question #1495 because ... there won\\\'t be another Pivot available during that Jam because there is only one per Jam per team, so the answer has to be \\\'any other skater from her team who will then serve as the Pivot\\\'', 3),
(342, '87.194.199.126', 1356880650, 1366, 0, 'Question #1366: I\\\'m reporting question #1366 because ... Major Cutting, yes, unless it\\\'s a team mate in which case NI/NP. :-)', 2),
(343, '90.38.118.163', 1356886298, 35, 0, 'Question #35: I\\\'m reporting question #35 because ... \\"2.1.5 - There will be a 10-foot (3 meter) clearance around the outside of the track for safety. If there is a rail, wall, or barrier between the track and the crowd that completely prevents contact between spectators and contestants, a 5-foot (1.5 meter) clearance is permissible. Referees may skate in this area, and/or the infield of the track. The clearance cannot be less than 5 feet (1.5 meters).\\"\r\n\r\nAnd especially this : \\"The clearance cannot be less than 5 feet (1.5 meters).\\"', 1),
(344, '82.38.253.42', 1356888662, 1083, 0, 'Question #1083: I\\\'m reporting question #1083 because ... it provides an incorrect answer. You\\\'ve quoted 3.5.5 which states \\"Jammer status is transferred when the Pivot is wearing the Jammer helmet cover on their helmet with the stars visible.\\" This would make the correct answer selection A.', 2),
