(352, '66.140.33.57', 1356922680, 1413, 0, 'Question #1413: I\\\'m reporting question #1413 because ... The rule says to penalize the skater who is most responsible or the pivot, not all skaters.  The part about the further penalties using 6.10.12 and 6.10.16 does not necessarily apply based on the limited information of the question.  Maybe add a D answer saying, \\"The skater most responsible or the pivot.\\"\r\n\r\nThanks!  Awesome test questions otherwise!', 2),
(353, '50.43.31.230', 1356924588, 86, 0, 'Question #86: I\\\'m reporting question #86 because ... a new jam could also be declared at the head referees discretion in the case of an injury.', 3),
(354, '120.151.24.33', 1356933143, 1093, 0, 'Question #1093: I\\\'m reporting question #1093 because ... It doesn\\\'t mention centimeters, only inches. One of the major changes was to metric-ize everything, and everywhere EXCEPT for the US is now treating the metric measurements as gospel.  I got that one wrong because I was thinking \\\'shit, how big is 5cm in inches?\\\'', 3),
(355, '120.151.24.33', 1356935389, 258, 0, 'Question #258: I\\\'m reporting question #258 because ... This one also doesn\\\'t have the metric numbers, it\\\'s only in inches. ', 3),
