(478, '24.32.68.9', 1359009317, 1493, 0, 'Question #1493: I\\\'m reporting question #1493 because ... it is written in a confusing manner and can be interpreted incorrectly:\r\n\r\n True or False: A Fouled Out skater can be substituted in the jam if they Foul Out in order to prevent their team skating short.\r\n\r\nI know that another skater from the team of the fouled out skater can not be substituted during an on-going jam, but it sounds like the question is asking if a skater can foul out in order to prevent their team from skating short-which is not helping their team because now thier team is short one skater.  :)  I know that\\\'s not what the question is asking, but I had to re-read it a couple times to understand that the question was asking about substitutions during a jam for a fouled out skater.', 3),
