(497, '24.32.68.9', 1359664559, 1188, 0, 'Question #1188: I\\\'m reporting question #1188 because ... \r\n\r\nIt would be more correct if it said A skater intentionally uses their elbow to make contact with an opposing skater in an illegal manner. This is a/an:\r\n\r\nThe original rule states:\r\n6.4.10 - Intentional, negligent, or reckless contact with an opponent by using the elbow in an illegal manner.\r\n\r\nI would like to include:\r\n6.4.6 - Any illegal contact with the elbow or swinging motion of the elbow that forces the receiving opposing skater off balance, forward, and/or sideways but does not cause the opposing skater to lose relative position.\r\n\r\n6.4.6 is a no impact/no penalty if the receiving opposing skater is forced off balance, forward, and/or sideways but does not cause the opposing skater to lose relative position. So, unless the elbow was intentional and illegal it might be a no impact/no penalty if the receiving opposing skater did not lose their relative position. Also, according to 9.3.4 - If the referee is not sure whether an action warrants a major or a no impact/no penalty, it must be called as no impact/no penalty. So It depends on whether the elbow contact was illegal to decide what penalty would be given.\r\n\r\nThanks! I\\\'m not trying to be rude, but make the question more clear and irrefutable.', 3),
(498, '24.32.68.9', 1359665104, 1237, 0, 'Question #1237: I\\\'m reporting question #1237 because ... \r\n\r\nThere\\\'s a word missing that could throw people off:\r\nOriginal question:\r\nA skater repeated use obscene, profane, or abusive language or gestures directed at an official will be subjected to a/an:\r\n\r\nFixed versions (corrected/added word(s) in capital letters):\r\n-A skater THAT repeatedLY useS obscene, profane, or abusive language or gestures directed at an official will be subjected to a/an:\r\n-A skater repeatedLY useS obscene, profane, or abusive language or gestures THAT ARE directed at an official will be subjected to a/an: \r\n\r\nHope this helps. :)', 3),
(499, '166.147.121.160', 1359666975, 1219, 0, 'Question #1219: I\\\'m reporting question #1219 because ...  It has some pretty ambiguous language. A misconduct act does not necessarily mean a Misconduct penalty. I would change \\"act\\" to \\"penalty\\". ', 2),
