(544, '192.197.82.203', 1361462433, 946, 0, 'Question #946: I\\\'m reporting question #946 because ... In the Glossary the WFTDA definition of out of bounds is \\"A skater is out of bounds when any part of the skater’s body or equipment is touching the ground beyond the track boundary.\\"\r\n\r\nWhile the answer is technically correct, it gives the impression that you need two skates off the track to be considered out of bounds. It\\\'s a good trick question, but may add to some general confusion about \\"out of bounds\\" status as well.', 3),
(545, '71.216.40.171', 1361475634, 1057, 0, 'Question #1057: I\\\'m reporting question #1057 because ... \r\n\r\nIt seems that this question is contextual in that it depends on where the player is lined up. see below \r\n\r\n3.2.2.3 - A skater lined up in the Pivot starting position will not be considered a Pivot unless the skater is wearing or holding a helmet cover with a visible stripe.', 3),
