(558, '92.26.173.122', 1362957814, 1524, 0, 'Question #1524: I\\\'m reporting question #1524 because ... \r\nThe jammer is lapped by the pack, then they engage and pass through in derby direction - that is their initial pass, so they pass through once. Immediately they exit the front engagement zone their next pass begins which would be a scoring one. \r\n\r\nPut another way, the pack passing the jammer doesn\\\'t count i.e. jammer can\\\'t fail to move off the line, be lapped by the pack then skate forward and start scoring but the first time the jammer makes their way legally through the pack is their initial pass.', 1),
