(625, '131.130.15.0', 1369241283, 1581, 0, 'Question #1581: I\\\'m reporting question #1581 because ... \r\n\r\nAlthough it is consistent with the wording of rule 3.4.2.3, it is not true generally: to earn lead it is sufficient to pass legally all in-play blockers. So it is possible to pass only some blockers legally (those that are in play) then earn lead. It is mentioned in rule 3.4.1.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the word \\"blockers\\" should be used instead of \\"players\\", otherwise it implies that the opposing jammer must also be passed legally. I don\\\'t think you can fail to earn lead because of a no pass/no penalty on the opposing jammer.', 2),
