(643, '24.42.249.159', 1371158629, 870, 0, 'Question #870: I\\\'m reporting question #870 because ... it is poorly written. the first answer states that hand signals must be clear and designated. the correct answer is official designated hand signal. if a referee is using hand signals it already would be designated to be recognized. secondly the better answer should contain clear signals because doing some flapping arm motion that is unrecognizable is not followed because while it might be the official sign no one read it.', 3),
