(645, '68.43.74.97', 1371314551, 1208, 0, 'Question #1208: correct answer, but 6.5.9 describes it. Not 6.5.11 (that only refers to an opponent)', 2),
(646, '94.234.170.60', 1371452795, 1377, 0, 'Question #1377: I\\\'m reporting question #1377 because ... \r\nThere seems not be any rule 6.11.16!', 4),
(647, '209.128.31.118', 1371518822, 19, 0, 'Question #19: I\\\'m reporting question #19 because ... \r\nthe question says \\"true or false: the track boundary must be flat\\" which is true as per rule 2.1.2. However, when I clicked on True, it told me I was wrong and the correct answer was false and directed me to rule 2.1.3 which talks about track boundary. ', 1),
(648, '69.129.234.126', 1371674984, 1289, 0, 'Question #1289: I\\\'m reporting question #1289 because ... Which skater is \\"their skate\\" referring to, the initiator or the receiver?', 3),
(649, '69.129.234.126', 1371675092, 855, 0, 'Question #855: I\\\'m reporting question #855 because ... That\\\'s \\"one\\" role, but not the sole and only role.  Specifically, the jam timer also starts the jam.', 3),
(650, '69.129.234.126', 1371679150, 1342, 0, 'Question #1342: I\\\'m reporting question #1342 because ... I think you mean section 6.12.8 - Skating out of bounds to maintain or increase speed.', 3),
(651, '69.129.234.126', 1371679305, 1309, 0, 'Question #1309: I\\\'m reporting question #1309 because ... It\\\'s very unclear what\\\'s being asked.  Since this is under direction of gameplay, it might be helpful to include a note in the question that they\\\'re not only spun around but are now moving clockwise as the result of a block.  Otherwise being spun around as the result of a block *and still moving counter-clockwise* isn\\\'t a penalty at all.', 3),
(652, '74.133.214.4', 1371704564, 1661, 0, 'Question #1661: I\\\'m reporting question #1661 because ... it says \\"on in play teammate\\" instead of \\"one in play teammate\\" in the question. Thanks for making the awesome testomatic available to everyone. ', 3),
(653, '194.13.118.4', 1371737465, 1346, 0, 'Question #1346: I\\\'m reporting question #1346 because ...\r\n\r\nAs far as I know, this has been clarified recently. Out of Play Blocking penalties can be given without a warning, Failure to reform/return cannot.\r\n\r\nCheers!\r\nRoger.', 2),
(654, '67.189.28.213', 1371822851, 1661, 0, 'Question #1661: In-play/out-of-play absolutely DOES matter when it comes to Cutting. You should see the rule you\\\'re quoting, which says \\"in-play teammate\\". The correct answer here is No Impact/No Penalty.', 2),
(655, '128.165.50.178', 1371831789, 1661, 0, 'Question #1661: I\\\'m reporting question #1661 because ... \r\nI believe it\\\'s incorrect. Yes, the removed the words \\"in play\\" from the major penalty, but the NI/NP section still clearly addresses OOP skaters as being not a penalty. That doesn\\\'t change during  no pack. Just the distinction from in-play to in-bounds.  So she would only be cutting a single teammate, for NI/NP', 3),
(656, '189.177.35.1', 1372135898, 1662, 0, 'Question #1662: I\\\'m reporting question #1662 because it\\\'s wrong, the answer should be a no impact/no penalty, the WFTDA rules clearly stand out that you may \\"cut\\" any out of play opposing or teammate skaters without obtaining a penalty. \r\n\r\n\\"Major Penalty\r\n\r\n6.11.14 - A skater cutting any opposing in-play skater.\\"  \r\n\r\nSource: \r\nhttp://wftda.com/rules/20130615/section/6.11', 2),
(657, '72.175.107.110', 1372363276, 1086, 0, 'Question #1086: I\\\'m reporting question #1086 because ... The rules state: \\"A panty may be recovered by skating in any direction, INCLUDING out of bounds if the panty itself is out of bounds\\"', 1),
(658, '37.160.40.65', 1372442330, 1000, 0, 'Question #1000: I\\\'m reporting question #1000 because You write not on the track and entirely in bounds in the question.\r\nyou should say NOT entirely in bounds or out of bounds, it will be more clear.\r\nthanks', 3),
(659, '2.217.228.97', 1372444081, 1656, 0, 'Question #1656: I\\\'m reporting question #1656 because ... \\"brake\\" not \\"break\\".', 3),
(660, '12.186.102.200', 1372446033, 1037, 0, 'Question #1037: I\\\'m reporting question #1037 because ... Two of the four maximum referees are Jam referees NOT Pack referees.\r\n\r\nThe answer to the question as asked would be 2 Pack referees. (9.1.4.1 - No more than two Pack Referees will be stationed inside the track.)', 2),
(661, '198.228.200.165', 1372456753, 1638, 0, 'Question #1638: I\\\'m reporting question #1638 because ... \r\n\r\nThe answer is option A, I believe. ', 2),
(662, '81.110.222.189', 1372802584, 1464, 0, 'Question #1464: I\\\'m reporting question #1464 because ... the rules reference if 7.2.8.3 (I looked it up because I got it wrong!)', 2),
(663, '125.168.207.5', 1373367516, 1643, 0, 'Question #1643: I\\\'m reporting question #1643 because ... 4.2.7 says that they can be moving, coasting or braking. This is impossible if they couldn\\\'t begin rolling at some point before the jam start whistle.', 3),
(664, '124.148.202.13', 1373374211, 1218, 0, 'Question #1218: I\\\'m reporting question #1218 because ... If the seat in question is not structurally sound, then it is the fault of the bout organiser for creating a health & safety hazard, not the skater who sat in the seat.', 1),
(665, '125.168.207.5', 1373542666, 1187, 0, 'Question #1187: I\\\'m reporting question #1187 because ... the rule referred to doesn\\\'t explain the answer', 1),
(666, '68.185.195.27', 1373728684, 1451, 0, 'Question #1451: I\\\'m reporting question #1451 because ... This actually references 7.2.5, but the question references 7.2.6 (which is about removal of gear in the penalty box)', 1),
(667, '124.170.29.176', 1373783786, 498, 0, 'Question #498: I\\\'m reporting question #498 because ... \r\nIt\\\'s ambiguous. Does it mean she MUST skate \\"counter clockwise out of bounds\\" (i.e. not clockwise out of bounds, and not counter clockwise in bounds, and not clockwise in bounds) or does it mean she \\"can skate counter-clockwise, but ONLY IF it\\\'s out of bounds (and not in bounds)\\"?', 3),
(668, '124.170.29.176', 1373784843, 277, 0, 'Question #277: I\\\'m reporting question #277 because ... \r\nThere should be a question mark after \\"where\\", otherwise you read on to the answers and it ends up all ungrammatical e.g.\r\nProximity to the pack is measured from where the rear-most part of the skater ?????', 3),
(669, '212.247.94.54', 1374149035, 1414, 0, 'Question #1414: I\\\'m reporting question #1414 because ... \r\n\r\nIt seems to have an extra \\"not\\" in there that inverses the meaning of the question.\r\n\r\nRule 6.13.38 reads: \\"At the jam-starting whistle, less than half of a team’s on-the-track Blockers are in position...\\"\r\n\r\nThe question reads: \\"At the jam-starting whistle the less than half of a team\\\'s Blockers are ***not*** in the correct position...\\"\r\n\r\nWhich means that a majority of skaters are in position, which means it should not be a penalty. Also note the extra \\"the\\" in the question (\\"the less than half\\").', 2),
(670, '212.247.94.54', 1374149855, 1328, 0, 'Question #1328: I\\\'m reporting question #1328 because ... \r\n\r\n6.9.23 is not the only relevant rule - the unnumbered paragraph below the Expulsion headline is also relevant, especially this part: \\"Expulsions will be issued for a conscious and forceful attempt to block an opponent in an egregious manner...\\"\r\n\r\nMeaning that when 6.9.23 says \\"Intentional, negligent, or reckless contact with an opponent while stopped on the track in an illegal manner.\\", that is not the only requirement - it also needs to be forceful and egregious. Based on the information given in the question, in my opinion it is not clear that this is the case, and in that case 9.3.5 directs us to call it as a Major.\r\n\r\nI guess it could be argued that intent is hard to read, and if the referee is entirely sure that it was intentional, it must be egregious, but I wouldn\\\'t necessarily agree.\r\n\r\nSorry if this is nitpicking, but I think the details of enforcement are important, not just the rules as written. :)', 3),
(671, '194.66.11.43', 1374154786, 1632, 0, 'Question #1632: I\\\'m reporting question #1632 because ... \r\n\r\nJust a typo:\r\n\r\nTrue or False: A team may challenge a number on a helmet, as it may be misinterpreted at a star.\r\n\r\nshould be misinterpreted AS a star\r\n\r\nHope this helps!\r\n', 3),
(672, '131.130.15.0', 1374670466, 85, 0, 'Question #85: I\\\'m reporting question #85 because ... \r\n\r\nThe correct answer is A. and not D.\r\n\r\nIf there are less than 30 seconds remaining on the period clock and a team requests a team timeout, then there may still be another jam in that period.', 3),
(673, '176.252.19.211', 1374788507, 1270, 0, 'Question #1270: I\\\'m reporting question #1270 because ... I think this needs a reword given the June 15th release that state\\\'s \\"severely off-balance, forwards or sideways\\" as any forwards or sideways movement could be determined to be a penalty depending how you read the rules. ', 3),
(674, '41.132.164.24', 1375154544, 1595, 0, 'Question #1595: I\\\'m reporting question #1595 because I think the answer is C and not B as the rule states:  4.2.3 *If a Pivot is not upright and on the Pivot Line, non-Pivot Blockers are not required to line up behind that Pivot.\r\n\r\nTherefore a non-pivot blocker would only be able to line up in front of the pivot when the pivot is upright and on the pivot line.\r\n\r\n**Just a thank you for creating this! I\\\'m sure a ton of work has gone into it and it\\\'s really helping me with learning the rules :)', 1),
(675, '201.37.146.95', 1375210002, 1623, 0, 'Question #1623: I\\\'m reporting question #1623 because ... \r\n\r\nThe question is incomplete, leads to interpretation. It was simply taken out of context from rules and it is not accurate by itself.\r\n\r\nThe position of a Pivot can be transfered between Jams but it can\\\'t during a Jam.', 3),
(676, '176.253.128.166', 1375285502, 1270, 0, 'Question #1270: I\\\'m reporting question #1270 because ... I think this needs a reword given the June 15th release that state\\\'s \\"severely off-balance, forwards or sideways\\" as any forwards or sideways movement could be determined to be a penalty depending how you read the rules. ', 3),
(677, '176.253.128.166', 1375285604, 1270, 0, 'Question #1270: I\\\'m reporting question #1270 because ... I think this needs a reword given the June 15th release that state\\\'s \\"severely off-balance, forwards or sideways\\" as any forwards or sideways movement could be determined to be a penalty depending how you read the rules. ', 3),
(678, '150.226.95.18', 1375469217, 302, 0, 'Question #302: I\\\'m reporting question #302 because ... there is an exception to this rule. \r\n\r\nhttp://wftda.com/rules/qa/blocking-during-a-no-pack--updated-62613\r\n\r\nIn June WFTDA announced you do not have to physically move if you are meeting the requirement to reform.', 3),
(679, '95.195.131.160', 1375475979, 301, 0, 'Question #301: I\\\'m reporting question #301 because ... \r\n\r\nIt doesn\\\'t make sense to give an Out of Play warning before issuing a Failure to *Reform* penalty. I think the question is meant to say \\"Failure to Return\\".', 3),
(680, '95.195.131.160', 1375477040, 1167, 0, 'Question #1167: I\\\'m reporting question #1167 because ... \r\n\r\nSorry if this is nitpicking, but the question doesn\\\'t make it explicitly clear that the two skaters are from different teams. If they were from the same team, it would be NI/NP. I suggest changing their names to Red Blocker and Blue Blocker, or something along those lines. :)', 3),
(681, '76.95.44.99', 1375764951, 1064, 0, 'Question #1064: I\\\'m reporting question #1064 because ...  3.2.2.2 states the pivot only needs to have it in their hand when the jam starts to be the pivot and 3.2.2.3 states the pivot panty must have a stripe ', 3),
(682, '90.231.72.13', 1375803424, 1116, 0, 'Question #1116: I\\\'m reporting question #1116 because ... \r\n\r\nThe alternative \\"On track\\" is not incorrect, just imprecise - blockers should after all be on the track at jam start. I suggest changing it to \\"Anywhere on the track\\".\r\n\r\n(It could be argued that \\"On track\\" is incorrect since some blockers might be in the penalty box, but if so then all alternatives are equally incorrect.)', 3),
(683, '95.195.157.32', 1375823241, 1665, 0, 'Question #1665: I\\\'m reporting question #1665 because ... \r\n\r\nIt\\\'s poorly written and hard to read. Suggested replacement:\r\n\r\nRed skater is blocked out of bounds by an opponent considered to be \\"in the box\\" due to a prior penalty, then re-enters the track in front of the initiator. What penalty is assessed to Red skater?', 3),
(684, '95.195.157.32', 1375825505, 569, 0, 'Question #569: I\\\'m reporting question #569 because ... \r\n\r\nThe question does not state that the initiator is a blocker. In case the initiator was a jammer, she does not lose her ability to draw a cut on the opponent by exiting the EZ. Suggested replacement text:\r\n\r\n\r\nTrue or False: A skater may return in bounds in front of a blocker who blocked them out of bounds if the initiating blocker exits the Engagement Zone at any time after the initial block.', 3),
(685, '152.43.51.84', 1375892023, 1376, 0, 'Question #1376: I\\\'m reporting question #1376 because the \\\'Note\\\' is incorrect:\r\n\r\n\\"Note: It doesn\\\'t matter if a skater is in or out of play when it comes to Cutting penalties.\\"\r\n\r\nIt *does* matter if a skater is in or out of play:\r\n\r\nNo Impact / No Penalty\r\n\r\n6.11.4 - A skater who has returned to the track in front of a downed, out of bounds, or out of play skater is not bettering their position. However, such skaters are subject to cutting the track penalties for other in-play skaters and are still subject to skating out of bounds penalties.', 3),
(686, '67.170.93.34', 1376261636, 855, 0, 'Question #855: I\\\'m reporting question #855 because ... jam timers also time penalties. ', 1),
(687, '92.252.70.145', 1376471268, 1616, 0, 'Question #1616: I\\\'m reporting question #1616 because ... \r\nThat is confusing, because wftda clarification says that if there are 30 or less seconds on the period clock, Official Timeouts should not be taken.\r\n\r\nhttp://wftda.com/rules/qa/no-additional-jam-after-official-timeout', 4),
(688, '122.62.177.127', 1376471469, 880, 0, 'Question #880: I\\\'m reporting question #880 because ... \r\nThe referees must break up fights according to 9.2.6.2 - \r\nA referee must call off a jam for any of the following reasons:\r\n\r\n9.2.6.2.4 - Fighting.\r\n\r\nSo it is not at the discretion of the referee to break up a fight, he must  break up the fight, there for the statement is false.', 1);
INSERT INTO `rdtom_reports` (`ID`, `IP`, `Timestamp`, `Question_ID`, `User_ID`, `Text`, `Status`) VALUES
(689, '209.234.184.162', 1377038838, 1158, 0, 'Question #1158: I\\\'m reporting question #1158 because ... I reviewed the WFTDA rule, and it is stated this way, so maybe no change is required.  However, I found the wording of this question confusing.  How would you know if the player is making an attempt to contact the opposing skater above the shoulders if their attempt failed?', 4),
(690, '209.234.184.162', 1377040908, 331, 0, 'Question #331: I\\\'m reporting question #331 because ... The wording is confusing.  I chose option B (the skater who moves to make the contact) because I was considering positional blocking.  You can initiate positional blocking without making contact and you are still responsible for your positional block because you initiated.  I think this is WFTDA wording issue more than a testomatic issue, but still confusing wording.', 3),
(691, '24.209.242.160', 1377127268, 495, 0, 'Question #495: I\\\'m reporting question #495 because ... I don\\\'t believe there is any rule about them engaging in any way with their own teammates while skating clockwise.', 1),
(692, '65.183.129.195', 1377535784, 523, 0, 'Question #523: I\\\'m reporting question #523 because ... \r\n\r\nfailure to return also requires a warning now.\r\nhttp://wftda.com/rules/20130615/section/9.3\r\n\r\n\\"9.3.1.1 - A warning does not have to be issued in order for a penalty to be given. The exception to this is Out of Play Penalties for failure to reform and failure to return, before which warnings must be given. (See Section 6.10.6, Section 6.10.7, Section 6.10.12, Section 6.10.13, and Section 6.10.16 for exceptions.)\\"', 3),
(693, '81.56.1.251', 1377537345, 1693, 0, 'Question #1693: Only some Out of Play penalties needs a warning (failure to reform, failure to reenter). The warning are not necessary for the other out of play penalties (OOP block/assist, destroying the pack, illegal return)', 3),
(694, '24.9.236.13', 1378323878, 1488, 0, 'Question #1488: I\\\'m reporting question #1488 because ... The math doesn\\\'t seem to add up', 1),
(695, '131.130.15.0', 1378979834, 496, 0, 'Question #496: I\\\'m reporting question #496 because ... \r\n\r\nSaying that B is the correct answer and that D is incorrect implies that it\\\'s ok to block downed opponents if you are stopped (but it\\\'s not). Overall the answers are poorly formulated (so are the rules).', 3),
(696, '184.96.29.236', 1379997915, 523, 0, 'Question #523: I\\\'m reporting question #523 because ... on another question that seemed to be worded the same, it stated that they must give a warning and sited 6.10.6 ', 4),
(697, '68.64.53.227', 1380058883, 1508, 0, 'Question #1508: I\\\'m reporting question #1508 because the rules have changed allowing expelled skaters to remain at the track as long as they don\\\'t have an impact on the game.', 1),
(698, '219.90.166.64', 1380076343, 1528, 0, 'Question #1528: I\\\'m reporting question #1528 because ... Hey I got this wrong and when i followed the link and read the rule i understand that the jammer scores the points of the box upon passing an opposing blocker but i still dont understand what the question is asking me\r\n\r\nThank you this is an awesome tool to learn with!!\r\nRegards,\r\nDude of Hazard \r\nLight City Derby', 3),
(699, '68.64.53.227', 1380144545, 1508, 0, 'Question #1508: I\\\'m reporting question #1508 because the rules have changed allowing expelled skaters to remain at the track as long as they don\\\'t have an impact on the game.', 1),
(700, '110.142.118.76', 1381381488, 1433, 0, 'Question #1433: I\\\'m reporting question #1433 because ... \r\nIt is misleading.\r\nThree blockers may NOT be seated - they may serve penalties at the same time i.e. if one blocker stands at 10 seconds, a third blocker may be seated. \r\n\r\nA better reference would be:\r\n7.2.3.3 - If there are already two Blockers in the box from the penalized Blocker’s team, the third Blocker will be waved off by the penalty timer. If there are less than 10 seconds left on penalties currently being served, the penalty timer will hold the third Blocker in the box and start timing the penalty. If the skater is waved off, the skater must return to the track as described in Section 7.2.8. A Jammer can never be waved off from the penalty box.\r\n\r\nA better phrase may be:\r\nA team may have three blockers serving penalties in the penalty box at one time.', 3),
(701, '115.188.239.95', 1381912266, 1670, 0, 'Question #1670: I\\\'m reporting question #1670 because ... Not all skaters can retrieve helmet covers. Question should specify which cover and Pivot or Jammer.', 3),
(702, '207.126.248.6', 1381958827, 1329, 0, 'Question #1329: I\\\'m reporting question #1329 because ... 6.9.22 says \\"intentional\\" not \\"unintentional\\", so I\\\'m not sure why a skater would be expelled for this one. Would they?', 3),
(703, '207.126.248.6', 1381963763, 1329, 0, 'Question #1329: I\\\'m reporting question #1329 because ... 6.9.22 says \\"intentional\\" not \\"unintentional\\", so I\\\'m not sure why a skater would be expelled for this one. Would they?', 3),
(704, '71.202.77.190', 1381975245, 1618, 0, 'Question #1618: I\\\'m reporting question #1618 because ... \\"Entirely\\" is spelled wrong throughout.', 3),
(705, '82.181.229.185', 1382039533, 1307, 0, 'Question #1307: I\\\'m reporting question #1307 because ... I\\\'d like to know which rule it is referring to :D ', 3),
(706, '32.170.115.140', 1382450302, 1441, 0, 'Question #1441: I\\\'m reporting question #1441 because ... \r\nThere is a spelling error. 7.2.3.3 says \\"A Jammer can never be waved off from the penalty box.\\" \r\nWaved not waived \r\n', 3),
(707, '32.152.190.138', 1382490598, 1533, 0, 'Question #1533: I\\\'m reporting question #1533 because ... \r\n8.5.1.1.1 - Opponents in the penalty box. (The moment a penalized skater is issued a penalty the skater is considered “in the box” for scoring purposes.)\r\n\r\nSo unless I\\\'m reading this wrong and blue jammer had already scored on red jammer one, wouldn\\\'t blue jammer only score one point because after it scores on red jammer two it can\\\'t score on red one because it is technically considered off the track and in the box?', 3),
(708, '89.80.119.131', 1382524792, 1171, 0, 'Question #1171: I\\\'m reporting question #1171 because there is an orthographic problem in the second phrase:\r\n\r\n\\"At what point will THEY get a Major Penalty?\\" does not fit with the D answear, because the right question should be \r\n\\"At what point will HE get a Major Penalty?\\"', 3),
(709, '150.226.95.18', 1382541961, 553, 0, 'Question #553: I\\\'m reporting question #553 because ... \\"One penalty will be applied to a single skater per team, if applicable, who seems most responsible, or the Pivot\\"   This question could be written better. The pivot historically is penalized more often, but not more heavily. ', 3),
(710, '50.98.208.121', 1382603999, 1538, 0, 'Question #1538: I\\\'m reporting question #1538 because ... \r\nthere  is no comma  placed in the  sentence thus lending itself to be read  several diferent ways.\r\nThis  appears to be  saying that if  that  blocker  has  not yet reached  engaement  zone  their point can not be earned when jammer  passes  1st opposing blocker  in  engagement  zone.\r\nIt reads  somewhat as a grey question  since  it is  not clear where  each  skater  is located  on  track  at  time  of  question.', 3),
(711, '50.98.208.121', 1382605394, 1354, 0, 'Question #1354: I\\\'m reporting question #1354 because ... \r\nthough  this  question is in direct reference  to the  rule 6.10.13 it  does  lend a  unique counter  question in  the  fact an out of  bounds  player  is  not  required to skate  clockwise to renter track  and  thus  should not be  assigned  a major  for not immediately returning to track if  an opposing  skater  is  behind  them who was in front at time of going out of bounds.\r\nI  see  this  as  something WFTDA needs  to address in its  wording of this rule more so then you changing or altering the question. But I think it  best to remove this question till WFTDA better  clarifies  this  rule.', 3),
(712, '76.126.165.254', 1382825430, 256, 0, 'Question #256: I\\\'m reporting question #256 because there are multiple correct answers - b, c and d and when I chose B, it says I\\\'m wrong! ', 1),
(713, '76.126.165.254', 1382918790, 1309, 0, 'Question #1309: I\\\'m reporting question #1309 because ... there\\\'s at typo - \\"touche\\" should be \\"touch\\"', 3),
(714, '101.168.255.244', 1383173702, 1157, 0, 'Question #1157: I\\\'m reporting question #1157 because ... the rule under June 15, 2013 publication is 6.2.3, not 6.2.4. ', 2),
(715, '77.250.202.249', 1383261830, 1656, 0, 'Question #1656: I\\\'m reporting question #1656 because ... \r\n\r\nAccelerate, not accellerate.', 3),
(716, '77.250.202.249', 1383262551, 1266, 0, 'Question #1266: I\\\'m reporting question #1266 because ... \r\n\r\nIt is WAIVED off and not waved.\r\nhttp://www.thefreedictionary.com/waived', 1),
(717, '77.250.202.249', 1383404706, 1309, 0, 'Question #1309: I\\\'m reporting question #1309 because ... \r\n\r\nThey incidentally touche another  - touch.', 3),
(718, '217.113.160.50', 1383657622, 77, 0, 'Question #77: I\\\'m reporting question #77 because ... The end of the fourth whistle, not the last of the four.', 3),
(719, '98.223.74.239', 1383778676, 1619, 0, 'Question #1619: I\\\'m reporting question #1619 because ... \\"entirely\\" is misspelled and \\"in front\\" is two words', 3),
(720, '81.65.88.44', 1383957795, 1109, 0, 'Question #1109: I\\\'m reporting question #1109 because ... \r\n\r\nSection 6.17.3 no longer exists in rules.\r\n\r\nThe good answer is now given by 6.16.12', 3),
