(769, '77.97.179.116', 1389915555, 1515, 0, 'Question #1515: I\\\'m reporting question #1515 because ... \r\n\r\nI believe the current correct answer of \\"Land on their skate in bounds and continue upright and skating\\" is incorrect.\r\n\r\nThe specific rule (8.3.1.2) doesn\\\'t state the jammer has to be skating afterwards. The WFTDA Q&A section has a question about this (http://wftda.com/rules/qa/passing-while-airborne--updated-62613) and that states the jammer can still receive the point(s) as long as the initial point of landing is in bounds. \r\n\r\nI believe the correct answer for this should be \\"Land on their skate, in bounds and with upright status at the moment of landing, regardless of whether they stay upright and skating\\". \r\n\r\nIf you could check this it would be appreciated.  Thank you. ', 2),
